snippet.textDisplay:
Dear friends over the world, here is something you need to know about the Wuhan Coronavirus.

Chinese doctor Li Wen-liang was the first person to reveal the virus outbreak and warned the public of it in January. He was then arrested and accused of spreading rumours. In February, he, diagnosed with Wuhan virus, passed away.

We could not blame anyone for the existence of virus, but we could definitely blame the officials who tried to cover up the huge public threat. To maintain the power of the regime, Chinese Communist Party would by all means whitewash all their faults and pretend as the ultimate victim. We are sympathetic to those Chinese people in need for sure, but our forgiveness is never applicable to CCP.

Dr. Tedros, the Ethiopian WHO Chief, has been the biggest fan of China ever since the outbreak of the virus. Do you ever doubt the relationship of him and the Chinese government? In the Belt and Road development plan initiated by China over the past few years, CCP promised to grant huge loans to poor countries (including those in Africa) for their infrastructure and economic development. Yet the result turned out to be the countries failing to repay the debts and having to sell their lands and harbours instead. As the biggest debt collector, China grabs the control over them, so you should know why Dr. Tedros won the WHO Chief election by getting all the votes from China’s allies.

Hong Kong and Taiwan are geographically closest to China, but are currently the places with lowest infection rates of Wuhan virus. As most people would agree, we are the ones who never trust China. The former is under her political suppression, while the latter is facing her military threat all the time. We all understand how CCP upholds their totalitarian power, by minimising any chance of undermining their strong image.

After bringing the virus all over the globe, the regime would just NEVER apologise for the trouble brought. They shirk their responsibility and pretend to be a hero who stands by all affected countries and states. The shameful act sounds ridiculous, yet this has happened long as experienced by us.

My words may be too long so here is words in short: CHINA IS THE CULPRIT AND DO NOT TRUST THEM.

Facing one of the most challenging and widespread pandemic, we Hongkongers will surely continue to stand together with you.

Let’s stay strong and unity would make things right.

snippet.textDisplay:
Funny how no reports are ever discussed on all the people recovering from this virus. Just constant "Doom And Gloom" reports on people catching it and how many died when in fact 98% recover from the symptoms. The regular Flu is much more dangerous than Covid-19 and even with a constantly changing vaccine for the Flu we still cannot stop this virus from killing 50 to 80,000 people every year, that's even WITH A FLU VACCINE people. As of todays date here in the USA the "Victoria" strain flu has killed
over 22,000 people and again that is with a very large percentage of the US population having undergone a vaccine. The good thing about the broad panic worldwide is that this will get people to disinfect/wipe things down and wash their hands who otherwise wouldn't generally do those two things.

The New York Times published an article on January 8th

"The Flu Season May Yet Turn Ugly, C.D.C. Warns"

If you care to Google this article they talk about this exact thing and also mention that in 2018 over 61,000 Americans died from the flu down from 79,000 the year before. These are the CDC.gov numbers.

https://www.cdc.gov/flu/about/burden-averted/2017-2018.htm#anchor_1574361280230
